condition. Especially after taking a little bit of a break with my back problem, it's a really positive sign for me to be at the front of the race again. We came into the last 500 metres and it had been quite fast until then. It wasn't a very steep finish but it was more explosive. I thought 'If I'm going to try anything, it might as well be here'. I gave it a little push but the main contenders all followed my wheel and accelerated past me. I'm happy I tried but I know I've got a lot of work to do on my condition.\"</p><p>Quintana, Rodríguez and Contador were Froome's closest challengers during last year's Tour de France triumph and are expected to be his main rivals in his year's race, which begins in Yorkshire on 5 July.</p><p>The fourth stage on Thursday will see the peloton travel 166km to the finishing climb and Froome is hoping he can gain immediate revenge. \"They rode the race very well tactically. I was the first to move out of all of them, which was probably not the right thing to do but I tried. I did my race and they did their race. My team-mates did a really good job. It was quite a difficult stage with the cold. All day they were going backwards and forwards getting hot tea and good clothing. I really need to say thank you to them.</p><p>\"I think tomorrow will be more my style of racing. Again I'm here after a big break so I'm just hoping to do the best race possible and just to get that race feeling back into the legs again.\"</p>","headline":"Chris Froome moves up to third place in Volta a Catalunya","trailText":"The Tour de France champion showed he is recovering well from a back injury","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/26/1395863499344/Chris-Froome-001.jpg","wordcount":"472","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-03-29T20:05:48Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2014/mar/26/chris-froome-third-place-volta-catalunya-third-stage","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/sport/